==English==
===Etymology===
Derives from Latin ''hiatus, -us, m.'': gap; cf. hiare, hio, hiavi (hisco); (&#967;&#945;&#943;&#957;&#969;) &#941;-&#967;&#945;&#957;-&#959;&#957;, &#954;&#941;&#967;&#951;&#957;&#945;; Old High German gin&#275;n; German 'gähnen' -> "yawn")

===Noun===
{{en-noun2|'''hiatus'''|'''[[hiatus]] '''or''' [[hiatuses]]'''}}

#A [[break]] or [[pause]]; a [[gap]] in a [[series]], making it [[incomplete]].
#(''linguistics'') A [[pause]] between same [[vowel]]s at the end and the beginning of a word, as in "co'operation".
#A [[gap]] in [[geological]] [[strata]].
#A [[fissure]] in a [[bone]].
#A small [[difference]] in [[pitch]] between two [[musical]] [[tones]].
#A [[temporary]] [[pause]] in such activities as [[blogging]] or [[column]] [[writing]].

====Synonyms====
*[[break]] (1)
*[[glottal stop]] (2)

